DEFINITIONS

"Software" means the ip-Solis source code, Docker images, documentation,
and all associated files in this repository.

"Active User" means a distinct natural person, identified by their email
address, who at a given point in time holds at least one active asset
request or assignment in the Software. Persons whose requests and
assignments have all ended (e.g. cancelled, expired, revoked, returned,
or otherwise terminated) are not counted.

"Free Use" means use of the Software without a license file, limited to:
(i) purely private use by natural persons outside any commercial,
professional, governmental, or other organizational activity;
(ii) time-limited evaluation for up to 30 days; (iii) non-productive
use for research and teaching purposes at state-recognized educational
and research institutions; and (iv) productive use with up to 25 Active
Users (the "Free Tier"), including in a commercial, governmental, or
other organizational context.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software beyond Free Use. In
particular, productive or operational use of the Software with more than
25 Active Users in the context of a commercial, freelance, governmental,
or other organizational activity is Commercial Use -- irrespective of any
intention to generate revenue or profit. The Free Tier (productive use
with up to 25 Active Users) does not by itself constitute Commercial Use,
regardless of the organizational context. Use with more than 25 Active
Users -- including by legal entities under public law (e.g. cities,
municipalities, public authorities, and public-law corporations and
institutions) as well as by tax-privileged or charitable organizations --
requires a commercial license.

GRANT OF RIGHTS

Subject to the terms below, XenPool GmbH grants you a worldwide,
non-exclusive, non-transferable license to:

1. Use, copy, and modify the Software for Free Use, including productive
   use within the Free Tier (up to 25 Active Users).
2. Evaluate the Software in any environment for up to 30 days without a
   license key.

COMMERCIAL USE REQUIRES A LICENSE

Any Commercial Use of the Software requires a valid commercial license
obtained from XenPool GmbH. To purchase a license, visit the ip-Solis
license shop:

  https://ipsolis.com/en/shop

A valid commercial license is evidenced by a signed .lic file issued by
XenPool GmbH and installed in the Software's license directory. Among
other parameters, the license defines its term and the maximum number of
Active Users permitted (the licensed volume band); a band of "0" means an
unlimited number of Active Users. The Software will operate with a 30-day
grace period after license expiry, after which it reverts to the Free Tier
until a renewed license is installed.

Enforcement is non-disruptive: existing operation continues, and once the
applicable Active-User limit is reached -- 25 in the Free Tier, or the
licensed band where a commercial license is installed -- the Software
prevents the creation of access for additional, previously-uncounted users
until usage falls below the limit or a license covering the required band
is installed.

RESTRICTIONS

Without a valid commercial license you may not:

1. Use the Software for Commercial Use.
2. Remove or alter any copyright, trademark, or license notices.
3. Sublicense, sell, rent, or distribute the Software to third parties
   for commercial purposes.
4. Use the Software to offer a competing hosted or managed service.

MODIFICATIONS AND CONTRIBUTIONS

You may modify the Software for your own Free Use. Modified
